Key Match Events: Quinton de Kock made 109 runs in 106 balls
Kagiso Rabada took three wickets for 33 runs
Marco Jansen took two wickets for 54 runs
Keshav Maharaj took two wickets for 30 runs
Marnus Labuschagne made 46 runs, the only top-order batsman to score significantly for Australia
Australia lost their first five wickets for 65 runs
Glenn Maxwell took two wickets for 34 runs
Adam Zampa removed Rassie van der Dussen for 26 runs
Mitchell Starc took two wickets for 53 runs in the final over
Pre-Game Insights: Australia captain Pat Cummins won the toss and elected to field
Temba Bavuma's laidback South Africa seemed a different World Cup proposition
Post-Match Reflections: Australian captain Pat Cummins acknowledged South Africa's strong batting performance
Cummins expressed that finding ways to challenge in all conditions is necessary for future success
Miscellaneous Highlights: Quinton de Kock picked up where he left off in the defeat of Sri Lanka
Adam Zampa's delivery was described as zipping around more than during the day
The Australian bowlers put the brakes on South Africa's scoring rate
